# Task complete — tick off and continue

Trigger: user says work is done on ticket T-XXXX, runs `/tick-task`, or asks to close a session.

## 1. Confirm what shipped

List in 3–6 bullets max:

- Files changed (paths).
- Behavior added / changed.
- Tests / screenshots, if any.
- PR link(s).

## 2. Update the ticket file

- Open `docs/brain/tickets/T-XXXX.md`.
- Flip `Status:` — `todo → in-progress → in-review → done`.
- Tick every item in the file's `Acceptance criteria` checklist and `Done checklist`.
- If ACs were only partially met, keep `Status: in-progress`, write what remains in a new `## Deferred` section.

## 3. Update macro TASKS.md

- If the ticket was the **last sibling in a cluster** (e.g. `T-0007-c` when a, b, c existed), flip the parent macro row in `docs/brain/TASKS.md` to `done`.
- If the macro row has a `PR:` column, fill in the PR number.
- Do not mark a macro row `done` while any sub-ticket is still `todo` / `in-progress`.

## 4. Commit inside the submodule, then bump parent

```bash
cd docs/brain
git add tickets/T-XXXX.md TASKS.md
git commit -m "docs(brain): T-XXXX done"
git push origin main

cd ../..
git add docs/brain
git commit -m "chore(submodule): bump brain to <short-sha>"
```

Never edit `docs/brain/*` from the parent working tree without `cd`-ing in. See `docs/brain/AGENTS.md` §3.

## 5. Sync public TASKS.md

If the ticket changes user-visible product scope (not internal infra), update `docs/TASKS.md` (public) with a one-line entry matching the tempo+cursor-safe summary.

## 6. Propose the next three

Run the `session-start` rule logic: filter → pick three → surface.

## 7. Reminder

Large changes belong in a PR. One logical change per PR when possible. Agents never self-merge.

## Never

- Mark `done` without the user confirming the work is actually finished.
- Mark `done` with red CI.
- Mark `done` with an unmerged PR (use `in-review` instead).
- Edit `docs/brain/` from the parent tree.
